The paper deals with the study of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) interference channels (ICs) with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of output feedback and retrospective interference alignment, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves the analysis of DoF regions, which is a common theme in optimization and game theory (cs.MM) and communication engineering (cs.CE).
